BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:hZahZmnNeFxVIRM12xPUf
SUMMARY:Ratboys
DTSTAMP:20260326T005802Z
DTSTART:20260408T020000Z
DESCRIPTION:Neumos Presents \n\nWhen The Sun Explodes Tour\n\nRATBOYS\n\nvi
	llagerrr\n\nTUE\, 7 APR 2026 at 07:00PM PDT\n\nAges: 21 & Over\n\nDoors Op
	en: 07:00PM\n\nOnSale: Fri\, 26 Sep 2025 at 07:00AM PDT\n\nAnnouncement: T
	ue\, 23 Sep 2025 at 07:00AM PDT\n\nRatboys present a momentous new single\
	, “Light Night Mountains All That\,” and announce a North American tour.\n
	\nThis is the band’s first new music\, and their first with New West Recor
	ds\, since The Window\, one of the most-praised albums of 2023. The Window
	 catapulted the band from being beloved to “feverishly fixated upon” \\(St
	ereogum\\)\, and “Light Night Mountains All That” seizes that attention an
	d doesn’t let it look away.\n\nThe Window received a wealth of critical pr
	aise from the likes of The New York Times\, NPR Music\, Rolling Stone\, Bi
	llboard\, Stereogum\, and Uproxx\, while Pitchfork called it "a level-up r
	ecord" for the band.\n\n“Light Night Mountains All That” is singer/guitari
	st Julia Steiner’s most thrilling vocal take yet\, bolstered by a powerhou
	se performance by guitarist Dave Sagan\, drummer Marcus Nuccio\, bassist S
	ean Neumann\, and piano by track co-producer Chris Walla. The track\, deem
	ed their “wormhole jam” by Steiner\, is driven by an unorthodox time struc
	ture\, exhilarating instrumentation\, and the flare of extraterrestrial gu
	itar bloops.\n\nIn early 2026\, Ratboys will perform across North America.
	 As Paste praises\, Ratboys have “a live chemistry that remains unparallel
	ed and irreplaceable.”\n\nImportant Information:\n\n \\* This event is 21 
	& over. Valid ID is required. Minors will not be permitted entry.\n\n \\* 
	Doors open at the listed event time.\n\n \\* Event start time is generally
	 one hour after doors open but is subject to change without notice.\n\n \\
	* All tickets are nonrefundable with the exception of event cancellation.\
	n\n \\* Support acts are subject to change.\n\n \\* Orders in violation of
	 the published ticket limit are subject to cancellation without notice.\n\
	nhttps://seatoday.6amcity.com/events/#/details/ratboys/17008229/2026-04-07
	T00\n\nFrom SEAtoday - Sports & Outdoors
URL:https://seatoday.6amcity.com/events/#/details/ratboys/17008229/2026-04-
	07T00
LOCATION:Neumos\, 925 E Pike St\, Seattle\, WA
X-CALRIPPER-SOURCE:seatoday-sports
CATEGORIES:SEAtoday - Sports & Outdoors
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT2H
END:VEVENT
